# Chrome Extension App Structure (MV3 + Side Panel)

**Goal:** Standardize structure for MV3 service worker, content scripts, side panel UI, and shared automation recipes so state stays reliable across navigations.

> Build context: Vite multi-entry builds copy MV3 artifacts into `dist/` during `nx build`.

## Directory Layout (SummerySky example)

```text
apps/chrome-extensions/PMHNP-Administration-SummerySky/
├─ src/
│  ├─ service_worker/            # MV3 background orchestration + storage + messaging
│  ├─ content/                   # Content scripts (DOM extraction + guidance)
│  ├─ sidepanel/                 # Side panel UI (React)
│  ├─ popup/                     # Optional popup entry
│  ├─ recipes/                   # JSON recipes + loader/registry
│  ├─ utils/                     # Shared utilities
│  └─ tests/                     # unit/integration/e2e
├─ scripts/                      # manifest/build helpers
├─ vite.config.mjs               # UI bundle
├─ vite.config.content.ts        # content/service worker bundles
├─ tsconfig.json
├─ project.json                  # nx targets (build/test/e2e)
└─ README.md
```
